    <h3 class="subhead">FRENCH RITUAL</h3>
    <p>The French Ritual is comparable with the preparation of Pastis such as Pernod or Ricard, the follower or substitute for Absinthe after its prohibition. You put one or two sugar cubes on an Absinthe spoon, place it over the glass and fill it with an amount of Absinthe (2 to 4 cl). Then gently water is poured over the spoon. The green Absinthe begins to louche into white sage. In former times so called "Absinthe Fontaines" were widely used to dissolve the sugar with a thin beam of water which creates the perfect Louche.</p></div>

